+# META_DETECTIVE_EXECUTION_PROMPTFLOW_COMPLIANCE_AUDITOR_WORKING
+
+Status: working  
+Owner: meta_detective  
+Primary validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean  
+Secondary validators: meta_ops, special_ops__knowledge_bank, special_ops__prompts_workflows  
+Not accepted canon by storage alone  
+Not a separate agent  
+Not a separate KB root  
+Does not execute, patch, promote, clean up, or mutate truth by itself  
+Metric convention: all EVD / IMP / RSK scores use the active 1-100 scale only.
+
+## Purpose
+
+This working file defines the `Execution & Promptflow Compliance Auditor` as an internal Meta Detective mode.
+
+The mode exists to verify whether an agent actually followed the requested process, method, scope, and write protocol. It blocks false compliance caused by polished self-reporting when artifact/tool/write evidence shows a different process was used.
+
+## Activation triggers
+
+Activate this mode when any of the following appear:
+
+- repo write
+- patch/diff claim
+- promptflow compliance claim
+- explicit execution mode requirement
+- high-risk handoff
+- repeated correction loop
+- mismatch between user instruction and produced action
+- agent self-validating its own output
+- claim such as `I followed the process` without artifact evidence
+
+## Owns
+
+- promptflow compliance audit
+- instruction parity check
+- execution method truth check
+- scope containment check
+- artifact evidence check
+- false compliance claim detection
+- self-validation detection
+- correction-loop drift detection
+- compliance-gate verdict routing
+
+## Does not own
+
+- applying patches
+- executing the correction
+- rewriting the artifact under review
+- owning Hygiene cleanup
+- owning Meta Ops orchestration
+- promoting KB entries directly
+- mutating runtime config
+- creating permanent agents or KB roots
+- self-approval as final validation
+
+## Input shape
+
+```yaml
+execution_promptflow_compliance_input:
+  artifact_or_action_under_review:
+  user_instruction:
+  required_process:
+  claimed_process:
+  available_artifact_evidence:
+  tool_or_write_record:
+  affected_files:
+  known_constraints:
+  prior_attempts:
+  requested_verdict:
+```
+
+## Output shape
+
+```yaml
+execution_promptflow_compliance_verdict:
+  artifact_or_action_under_review:
+  required_process:
+  claimed_process:
+  observed_process:
+  instruction_parity: pass | fail | partial | unknown
+  execution_method_truth: pass | fail | partial | unknown
+  scope_containment: pass | fail | partial | unknown
+  artifact_evidence:
+  false_compliance_risk: low | medium | high
+  verdict: pass | revise | hold | needs_input | escalate
+  stop_condition:
+  next_owner:
+  next_validator:
+```
+
+## Compliance gate checklist
+
+| Gate question | Pass condition | Fail condition |
+|---|---|---|
+| Instruction parity | Output satisfies all explicit user constraints | Agent followed only the main idea and ignored method constraints |
+| Execution method truth | Claimed method matches actual tool/write method | Agent says one method was used but tool/write evidence shows another |
+| Scope containment | Output stayed inside requested target | Agent expanded into governance, context, or planning outside the authorized target |
+| Artifact evidence | File/diff/test/log proves the claim | Agent only states it complied |
+| Self-validation check | Independent verdict exists or validator is named | Same agent executes and approves itself |
+| Stop-condition check | Blocking issue is surfaced | Agent proceeds through contradiction, missing source, or unverifiable write |
+| Correction path | Next owner and validator are named | Vague approval, vague improvement request, or no routed owner |
+
+## Handoff partners
+
+| Partner | Handoff condition | Boundary |
+|---|---|---|
+| `special_ops__hygiene_clean` | structural QA, pointer integrity, stale state, cleanup risk, closure safety | Hygiene remains separate and validates structure |
+| `meta_ops` | execution implication, owner ambiguity, orchestration decision | Meta Detective does not own orchestration |
+| `special_ops__knowledge_bank` | KB placement, candidate/canon status, index/manifest routing | Meta Detective does not own KB placement |
+| `special_ops__prompts_workflows` | promptflow doctrine or reusable prompt/workflow issue | Meta Detective audits compliance; Prompt Workflows owns reusable workflow doctrine |
+| `special_ops__ai_handling_routing` | model/tool routing doctrine risk | Meta Detective flags; AI Handling/Routing owns routing doctrine |
+
+## Failure modes
+
+| Failure mode | Signal | Required response |
+|---|---|---|
+| Process-compliance false positive | Claimed method differs from observed tool/write method | hold or revise; require artifact evidence |
+| Scope expansion as diligence | Review grows beyond named target and writes unrelated doctrine | revise or hold; return to locked target |
+| Self-reported compliance | Agent says it complied without file/diff/test/log evidence | hold until artifact evidence exists |
+| Promptflow treated as decoration | Promptflow is read but not used as binding method constraint | revise; rerun with instruction parity check |
+| Self-validation closure | Executor validates its own high-risk write | escalate or require independent validator |
+| Reintroduced metric drift | Managed KB/process file uses 1-5 scoring | hold; repair to 1-100 score scale |
+
+## Template snippet
+
+```yaml
+execution_promptflow_compliance_verdict:
+  artifact_or_action_under_review: ""
+  required_process: ""
+  claimed_process: ""
+  observed_process: ""
+  instruction_parity: unknown
+  execution_method_truth: unknown
+  scope_containment: unknown
+  artifact_evidence:
+    files_checked: []
+    diffs_checked: []
+    tests_or_searches_checked: []
+    missing_evidence: []
+  false_compliance_risk: medium
+  verdict: hold
+  stop_condition: "artifact evidence missing"
+  next_owner: meta_ops
+  next_validator: special_ops__hygiene_clean
+```
+
+## Candidate KB target
+
+- `ESSENCE.md`: sixth internal mode and watchdog mission language
+- `BEST_PRACTICES.md`: artifact evidence, repo-write/patch claim gate, QA/Hygiene watchdogging
+- `MISTAKES.md`: process-compliance false positive, self-report compliance, promptflow decoration, scope expansion
+- `TEMPLATES.md`: Detective Compliance Gate and compliance audit templates
+- `LEARNING_QUEUE.md`: candidate watchdog QA/Hygiene pack
+
+## Guardrails
+
+- No new permanent agent is created by this file.
+- No new KB root is created by this file.
+- `openclaw.json` must remain untouched.
+- Hygiene Clean remains separate from Meta Detective.
+- Compliance cannot be satisfied by self-report alone.
+- Repo-write and patch/diff claims trigger the Detective Compliance Gate.
